       Hell Beast glance down at Inferno. His eyes flickered with internal 
repair and the new battery installment. Hell Beast didnt care if he was 
damaged, just as long as he could fire his gun.
       Then, he turned his attention to the small pellet holes in his armor 
caused by the assault from element, as well as the large baked gash on his 
upper leg. It hurt, but with the med kit tech fluid he could manage a little 
longer.
       Tankkor and Rampage squatted, if squatting is possible for bots that 
size, and kept a close watch on the battle unfolding yonder. They had taken 
temporary cover behinde what appeared to be a large metal plate once 
belonging to the CF, but had been torn off durring a past attack. Rampage 
turned to Hell Beast, "Ready?"
       He nodded. Hell Beast was taken care of, and Inferno was starting to 
come around agian. The four began to move.

       Craken, Pheniox, Aerostreak, and Gremlin rained down a mass of missle 
fire. Each blast shook the transformers, but the out come was a bright white 
explosion that nailed the CF's failing shields.
       "A few more, and we should be through!" Craken roared. He, the largest 
of the four, was in his vhicle mode as an assault helicopter and was looking 
out for any attackers. And wonders where Prowl went off too.

       Tarantulas, Waspinator, Aquarious, and Adrax huddled together for a 
moment. Adrax was bleeding, but he could withstand it for now. f it got worse 
he would have to clot it with something. As of now, they were under heavey 
fire, so, slowly, they poked up from a mass of smoking tree pulp and fired on 
the closest enemy. 

       Marine still watched for Iron Raptor. He was going to nail that fem, 
hard. She left gashes all over his chest that was now streaked with mech. 
Ominous Prime and two of his Energonians had joined Jackle, Nighteyes, and 
Klash as well. They aimed at the CF and watched as blue plasma and energon 
fire errupted on its surface.
